This is a web application built using Django that links Zendesk and Github for
easier developer management.

Setting up the application on Heroku:

1. Make an account on http://www.heroku.com/
2. Install the heroku toolbet using the command "wget -qO- https://toolbelt.heroku.com/install.sh | sh".
3. Install python and virtualenv. (A guide for this can be found at http://docs.python-guide.org/en/latest/starting/install/linux/)
4. Install a version of Postgres from http://www.postgresql.org/download/ so testing can be done locally.
5. Clone the GitZen repo with the command "git clone git://github.com/FriedRice/GitZen.git".
6. Change directories to the newly cloned GitZen directory and setup a virualenv using the command "virtualenv venv --distribute".
7. Activate the virtualenv with the command "source venv/bin/activate".
8. Run the command "sudo apt-get install libpq-dev python-dev" to install the necessary packages that allow for the installation of psycopg2 (Postgresql support for python) in the following step.
9. Install the required packages for GitZen and Heroku with pip by using the command "pip install -r requirements.txt".
